The Dipper: A Unique Tool and Ideal Travel Companion.

Firstly: as a designer, I really appreciate the work and attention to detail showcased in Dipstick Vapes Dipper. From the packaging down to the engineering, it’s look and feel ooze the quality and precision indicative of it’s price (149.99). Parts glide on-and-off seamlessly and it’s as easy to clean as it is to dismantle – another huge plus, especially when you’re on the go.

With imbibing cannabis still being a taboo pastime in the eyes of the uninitiated: discretion is a key selling point for any device.
With this in mind: a Dipper can be a great solution for indulging discretely while travelling. Smoking a joint in public can raise eyebrows and isn’t exactly easy to hide. Conversely: this device looks like Q gave it to you to subtly assassinate an ageing and well-guarded dictator.

The Dipper is far from traditional – and that’s what makes it exciting and unique. Not only is it a dipping device for dabbing, It also comes loaded with a ‘crystal quartz atomizer’ for your usual vape-action. Even with it being multi-functional it will still take away those common frustrations you get when packing your vape pen.

In short: The dipper is clean, well designed, easy to use, discrete and stylish. Shoutout to Dipstick Vapes for letting us take it for a test-drive, judging by the Dipper they have a very bright future indeed. @dipstickvapes
